[Topic]: Accept the market leader's acquisition offer?

[Financial Stabilization]: Fresh capital and a stronger group credit rating close the financing gap, securing survival from strength.
  +> [Topic]

[Capital Injection]: The deal brings immediate capital and better financing terms — relief the moment it is signed.
  +> [Financial Stabilization]

[Dismantling Risk]: The buyer may acquire the rival only to consolidate capacity, relocate the site and cut jobs.
  -> [Financial Stabilization]

[Operational Synergies]: Scale in procurement and production spreads fixed costs, lowering the cost per vehicle.
  +> [Topic]

[Procurement & Scale]: Larger purchasing volumes cut input costs and raise capacity utilisation — measurable, immediate savings.
  +> [Operational Synergies]

[Integration Costs]: Cultural friction and integration costs often eat the promised synergies.
  -> [Operational Synergies]

[Strategic Viability]: Stand-alone transformation is no longer viable; only integration secures long-run competitiveness.
  +> [Topic]

[Closing Window]: In moderate distress the firm still sets the terms; in 12–18 months the insolvency administrator negotiates instead.
  +> [Strategic Viability]

[Lost Upside]: Selling at the bottom hands the e-mobility recovery upside to the buyer.
  -> [Strategic Viability]
